				<outline text="Right now it's showing a &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/842769405268447232&quot;&gt;question mark&lt;/a&gt;." created="Sat, 18 Mar 2017 00:34:38 GMT" />
				<outline text="Here's what I did.&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;When the app is ready, where I create the new BrowserWindow, I added an icon value that is a NativeImage. Here's the &lt;a href=&quot;https://gist.github.com/scripting/b7a12552935e8454bf8e99babd4988f3&quot;&gt;code&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Here's the &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2017/03/17/pork.png&quot;&gt;PNG file&lt;/a&gt;. I didn't know what dimensions to make it so I made it large. It occurs to me that might be the problem.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The &lt;a href=&quot;http://pork.io/electric/linux/Electric-Pork-linux-x64.zip&quot;&gt;app&lt;/a&gt; launches, but the icon in the doc isn't what it should be.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;" created="Sat, 18 Mar 2017 00:34:39 GMT" />
